This paper is about domain adaptation for visual recognition, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves optimizing a theoretical error bound, which suggests a strong theoretical foundation and may be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of sparse regression, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE).
